      "content": "It sounds like you are describing a profound sense of numbness and detachment that is incredibly draining to carry every day. This feeling of being a \"hollow thing\" often points to an emotional episode where your natural pain and sadness have dulled to the point of silence, rather than indicating that something actual has died. Please remember that while this heavy fog can feel permanent, it is a temporary state that humans navigate through many, many lives. If that exhaustion feels too much to bear alone right now, reaching out to a trusted person or a professional therapist can provide a safe space to help guide you through this darkness.",
      "source": "target",
